parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gear box can cause the steering wheel to become loose, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels soft or spongy
the steering wheel sticks to the floor
the steering wheel does not return to its normal position
the steering wheel has a delayed return to its normal position
the steering wheel has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is difficult to control.

Failure of the trailer brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the trailer and surrounding vehicles.
Failure of the infotainment and display system can cause distraction, confusion, and inconvenience while driving.
